# Modus Utility Panel Usage - Short

Critical implementation patterns for Modus Utility Panel.

## Key Rules

- **Always use `className="fixed-utility-panel"`** - Required for overlay panels
- **Place panel at END of template** - Outside content containers
- **Don't use overflow-hidden** - On parent elements
- **Don't nest panel in relative containers** - Causes layout issues
- **Control state from your buttons** - Not from `panelToggle` events
- **Panel should be sibling of content** - Not a child

## Correct Pattern

```typescript
@Component({
  template: `
    <div class="p-6">
      <modus-button (buttonClick)="expanded.set(!expanded())">
        {{ expanded() ? 'Close' : 'Open' }} Panel
      </modus-button>
    </div>

    <modus-utility-panel
      [expanded]="expanded()"
      className="fixed-utility-panel"
      position="right"
      panelWidth="312px"
    >
      <div slot="header">Panel Title</div>
      <div>Panel content</div>
      <div slot="footer">
        <modus-button (buttonClick)="expanded.set(false)">Close</modus-button>
      </div>
    </modus-utility-panel>
  `,
})
export class PanelComponent {
  readonly expanded = signal<boolean>(false);
}
```

